Iavan Pijoos, News24 Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Durban - A Pretoria woman left her four-year-old son in her hot car while she went shopping at a KwaZulu-Natal mall on Friday afternoon, paramedics said.A concerned citizen noticed the boy in the car, in the parking lot at Tiffany&rsquo;s shopping centre, on the Dolphin Coast, and communicated with him through the small gap left open in the car&rsquo;s window, IPSS Medical Rescue spokesperson Paul Herbst said.&nbsp;The person waited with the child for 10 minutes before phoning emergency services.&nbsp;&ldquo;When confronted by the member of public, her response was that she does it all the time and it is perfectly safe,&rdquo; he said.&nbsp;The woman got into her car and sped off.Herbst appealed to members of the public not to leave young children or animals unaccompanied in hot vehicles.&ldquo;This is not an acceptable practice and emergency services will force entry into such vehicles.&rdquo;&nbsp; 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.